title: Virat Kohli flops on Ranji Trophy return - WATCH
text:
Virat Kohli flops on Ranji Trophy return - WATCH
Virat Kohli’s much-anticipated return to red-ball domestic cricket after more than 12 years ended in disappointment as he was dismissed for just six runs in Delhi’s
Ranji Trophymatch against Railways at the
Arun Jaitley Stadiumon Friday. Kohli walked in to bat at No. 4 on the second day of the match, with thousands of fans braving the chilly morning to witness the modern-day great in action. However, his stay at the crease was short-lived, lasting only 15 balls before he was clean-bowled by Railways pacer
Himanshu Sangwanin the 28th over.

A visibly disappointed Kohli walked back as some fans, equally dejected, exited the stands prematurely. Delhi, who had started steadily, were reduced to 86 for 3 in 27.4 overs following his dismissal.
Earlier on Day 1, Railways posted 241 in their first innings, with wicketkeeper-batter
Upendra Yadavanchoring the innings with a fighting 95 off 177 balls, including 10 fours and a six. Delhi’s bowlers had done well to restrict Railways, but their batting lineup now faced a stern test.
Kohli’s return to domestic cricket was expected to be a boost for Delhi, but his early exit came as a major disappointment. Fans will now hope for a better showing in the second innings as Delhi look to recover and take control of the match.
